    Speedy Fresh Basil Pesto & Tenderstem Broccoli Gnocchi

    We're bringing you all the green goodness with this Spring gnocchi pasta. We've got tenderstem broccoli, green beans and spinach. Plus, fresh basil pesto â€“ homemade with garlic, lemon and Sunflower seeds. Bring it together with fluffy potato gnocchi and tuck in.
    Cook time: 20 mins
    Cuisine: British
    Food group: Vegan
    Key ingredient: Fluffy potato gnocchi

    Ingredients

    • 1 handful of fresh basil
    • 2 garlic clove
    • 240g green beans
    • 1 lemon
    • 1 handful of fresh flat-leaf parsley
    • 80g rocket
    • 80g baby spinach
    • 10g sunflower seeds
    • 180g tenderstem broccoli
    • 500g potato gnocchi
    • 4 tbsp green pesto

    Nutritional Information

    Calories: 443
    Protein: 11g
    Carbs: 53g
    Fat: 20g

    Cooking Instructions

    Before you start
  • Pull out a large frying pan, a large saucepan, a small bowl & a sieve
  • Cook the greens
    • Trim the broccoli and green beans, then cut both into thirds
    • Heat the large frying pan with 1 tbsp oil over medium-high heat. Once hot, add the broccoli and green beans and cook for 5-6 mins, until beginning to char
    • Rinse the spinach, then add to the pan, along with a splash of water. Steam the veg for a further 1-2 mins, until the broccoli has softened and the spinach has wilted
  • Meanwhile, make the pesto
    • Roughly chop the parsley and basil. Finely chop or crush the garlic. Roughly chop the sunflower seeds and place half the seeds into the small bowl
    • Mix in the garlic, chopped herbs, green pesto, juice from the lemon (or to taste) and 2 tbsp oil. Season to taste
  • Gnocchi time
    • Bring the large saucepan filled with salted hot water to a boil
    • Once boiling, add the gnocchi and simmer for 2 mins, or until they float to the surface, then drain
    • Add the cooked gnocchi and pesto to the frying pan and mix to combine with the veggies. Gently toss through the rocket and season with salt and pepper to taste
  • Plate up
    • Serve the pesto gnocchi into bowls and scatter over the remaining sunflower seeds
